**2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE**

**2.1 Agent Hierarchy**

The system operates on a strict hierarchical model. QUANTUM is the
orchestrator with final authority over all publishing decisions.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Agent**    **Codename**   **Role**         **Primary Output**   **QA
                                                                    Authority**
  ------------ -------------- ---------------- -------------------- ---------------
  QUANTUM      Orchestrator   Plans, assigns,  Content briefs +     FINAL --- all
                              reviews,         approval decisions   gates
                              approves                              

  ELECTRON-1   Trend Scout    Discovers &      Ranked trend board   None (recommend
                              scores wellness  (7-15 trends/day)    only)
                              trends                                

  ELECTRON-2   Content        Generates        Full content package None (drafts
               Architect      scripts,         (10 fields)          only)
                              captions, CTAs                        

  ELECTRON-3   Video Producer Routes to video  AI video +           Pre-check only
                              tools, produces  storyboard +         
                              media            thumbnail            

  ELECTRON-4 / Publisher      Schedules &      Live                 Platform
  ORBIT                       publishes to     TikTok/IG/LinkedIn   compliance
                              social platforms posts                
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**2.2 Full Pipeline Flow**

Every piece of content follows this exact path from discovery to
publication:

9:30 AM Cairo --- E1 Trend Scout fires (cron)

↓ Discovers 7-15 wellness trends via RSS + Reddit + PubMed

↓ Scores trends (relevance, safety, freshness, module fit)

↓ Stores in trend_board table

↓ Auto-triggers QUANTUM via webhook

\~9:45 AM --- QUANTUM Planner fires (webhook)

↓ Reads trend_board

↓ Dedup check (sub-workflow) --- no duplicate topics

↓ Creates 3 content briefs (topic, module, platform, funnel, duration)

↓ Sends briefs to Telegram with \[Approve\] \[Reject\] buttons

\~10:00 AM --- Operator reviews on Telegram

↓ \[Approve\] → Brief Approval Handler triggers E2

↓ \[Reject\] → Brief archived, pipeline stops

\~30 seconds --- E2 Content Generator (webhook)

↓ Qdrant search: 15 brand rules + 71 banned phrases loaded

↓ Assemble Prompt v2 (dynamic CTA + platform tone + brand rules)

↓ Claude Sonnet 4 generates full content (10 structured fields)

↓ QA Gate 1: Health Claims (Haiku 4.5)

↓ QA Gate 2: Brand & Tone v2 (Haiku 4.5 + DO NOT FAIL safe list)

↓ QA Gate 3: Audience Fit v2 (Haiku 4.5 + 6 hard-coded checks)

↓ Cost tracked (input tokens, output tokens, e2_cost, qa_cost,
total_cost)

↓ Stored in content_logs table

↓ Content preview sent to Telegram with \[Publish\] \[Kill\] buttons

Operator decision --- Telegram

↓ \[Publish\] → E3 Video Producer triggered

↓ \[Kill\] → Content archived, no video produced

\~2-5 minutes --- E3 Video Producer (webhook)

↓ Routing logic: module + funnel + platform → video tool

↓ B2C Steps/Meals → Kling 2.6 via fal.ai

↓ B2C Workouts → Veo 3.1

↓ B2C Events/TikTok → Pika 2.2

↓ B2B Events/LinkedIn → Synthesia

↓ B2B default → HeyGen

↓ Video produced → stored in publish_logs

↓ Telegram preview sent

E4 Scheduler (every 5 min)

↓ Detects completed videos in publish_logs

↓ Video quality check (resolution, duration, format)

↓ Mode check: Manual / Semi-Auto / Full Auto

↓ \[Manual\] → Telegram platform selection buttons

↓ Operator selects TikTok / Instagram / LinkedIn / All

↓ schedule_logs entry created (status: queued)

ORBIT Publisher (every 5 min)

↓ Reads queued items from schedule_logs

↓ status → \'publishing\'

↓ Platform API calls: TikTok / Instagram Graph / LinkedIn

↓ status → \'published\' + platform_post_id + platform_post_url

↓ Telegram confirmation sent

↓ Dashboard Published tab updated

**2.3 Information Flow Between Agents**

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Stage**    **From**     **To**       **Data Passed**      **Mechanism**
  ------------ ------------ ------------ -------------------- ---------------------
  1\.          External     ELECTRON-1   RSS feeds, Reddit,   HTTP requests in E1
  Discovery    Sources                   PubMed               Code node

  2\. Curation ELECTRON-1   QUANTUM      Trend board (scores, Webhook POST
                                         labels, modules)     (auto-chained)

  3\. Brief    QUANTUM      Telegram +   3 briefs with full   Telegram Bot API +
  Creation                  DB           metadata             PostgreSQL INSERT

  4\. Approval Operator     Brief        Callback action:     Telegram
                            Approval     approve/reject       callback_query
                            Handler                           polling

  5\. Content  Brief        ELECTRON-2   Brief ID + brief     HTTP webhook POST
  Gen          Approval                  data                 
               Handler                                        

  6\. QA       ELECTRON-2   Telegram     Content preview (all Telegram Bot API
  Review                                 10 fields) + scores  (formatted message)

  7\. Publish  Operator     Brief        Callback action:     Telegram
  Decision                  Approval     publish/kill         callback_query
                            Handler                           polling

  8\. Video    Brief        ELECTRON-3   Content log ID +     HTTP webhook POST
  Production   Approval                  brief data           
               Handler                                        

  9\. ORBIT    ELECTRON-4   Telegram     Platform selection   Telegram Bot API
  Scheduling   Scheduler                 request              inline keyboard

  10\.         ORBIT        Social       Video URL +          TikTok / Instagram /
  Publishing   Publisher    Platforms    caption + hashtags   LinkedIn APIs
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

