**6. WORKFLOW DETAILS --- EXACT NODE NAMES FROM n8n**

**6.1 ELECTRON-1 Trend Scout (v1)**

Discovers trending wellness topics from 8 sources daily. Fires at 9:30
AM Cairo time (7:30 UTC). Auto-chains to QUANTUM via webhook.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**        **Detail**
  (exact)**                        
  ---------------- --------------- ------------------------------------------
  Schedule Trigger Schedule        Cron: 0 30 7 \* \* \* (UTC) = 9:30 AM
                   Trigger         Cairo (UTC+2)

  Webhook          Webhook         POST --- allows manual trigger via HTTP.
                                   Also used by auto-chain from E1 on
                                   re-runs.

  When clicking    Manual Trigger  For testing in n8n editor
  \'Execute                        
  workflow\'                       

  RSS Nerd Fitness RSS Feed Node   Pulls articles from Nerd Fitness RSS feed

  RSS MyFitnessPal RSS Feed Node   Pulls from MyFitnessPal blog RSS

  Reddit Fitness   HTTP Request    GET https://www.reddit.com/r/fitness/.json
                                   --- trending posts

  Reddit LoseIt    HTTP Request    GET https://www.reddit.com/r/loseit/.json
                                   --- weight loss trends

  RSS ACE Fitness  RSS Feed Node   Pulls from ACE Fitness blog RSS

  PubMed Search    HTTP Request    GET https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/\...
                                   --- research trends

  TikTok Trends    HTTP Request /  TikTok wellness trend signals
                   RSS             

  Instagram Trends HTTP Request /  Instagram wellness trend signals
                   RSS             

  Merge All        Merge Node      Mode: append --- combines all 8 source
  Sources                          outputs into one list

  Normalize Data   Code Node       Standardizes fields across all sources
                                   into uniform format

  Haiku Score      Code Node       Calls Claude Haiku 4.5 to score each trend
  Trends           (httpRequest)   0-100 by relevance, safety, module fit.
                                   Timeout: 120s.

  Store to         Code Node       Formats data for PostgreSQL INSERT
  trend_board                      

  Table:           PostgreSQL Node INSERT scored trends into trend_board
  trend_board                      table

  Trigger QUANTUM  Code Node       POST to QUANTUM webhook --- passes trend
                   (httpRequest)   board JSON to kick off brief creation
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Note:** The description sticky note in n8n reads: \'this is the trend
scout searching for trends in top 6 free sites then merge all results
format them then send them to Haiku to check the trend score if success
go to story board create the final items to be saved into table trend
board\'

**6.2 QUANTUM Content Planner (v1)**

Reads the trend board, builds a planner prompt, calls Claude Sonnet 4,
creates 3 briefs, inserts to DB, auto-triggers E2, and notifies
Telegram.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**        **Detail**
  (exact)**                        
  ---------------- --------------- ------------------------------------------
  Webhook          Webhook         POST --- primary trigger from E1\'s
                                   \'Trigger QUANTUM\' node

  Schedule Trigger Schedule        Fallback daily schedule trigger
                   Trigger         

  When clicking    Manual Trigger  For testing in n8n editor
  \'Execute                        
  workflow\'                       

  Execute a SQL    PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- reads current trend_board
  query                            for context

  Fetch Existing   PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- loads recent brief topics
  Briefs                           for dedup context

  Build Planner    Code Node       Assembles Claude Sonnet 4 prompt with
  Prompt                           trends + existing briefs + dedup
                                   instructions

  Call Sonnet      Code Node       Claude Sonnet 4 --- selects top trends,
  Planner          (httpRequest)   assigns module/platform/funnel/duration,
                                   outputs 3 briefs JSON

  Format Briefs    Code Node       Parses 3 brief objects from Claude
                                   response, structures for INSERT

  Insert Briefs    PostgreSQL Node insert --- adds 3 rows to content_briefs
                                   table (status: pending)

  Auto-Trigger E2  Code Node       Automatically POSTs to E2 webhook for each
                   (httpRequest)   approved brief --- no manual step needed

  Telegram Notify  Code Node       Sends 3 formatted brief messages to
                   (httpRequest)   Telegram with \[Approve\] \[Reject\]
                                   inline keyboard buttons
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.3 Brief Approval Handler (v1)**

The central Telegram controller. Polls every 30 seconds. Routes all
interactions through a Rules-based router into two branches: the
Approval Branch (for brief/content decisions) and the ORBIT Branch (for
scheduling/publishing decisions).

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**        **Detail**
  (exact)**                        
  ---------------- --------------- ------------------------------------------
  Schedule Trigger Schedule        Every 30 seconds --- polls Telegram for
                   Trigger         new updates

  manual trigger   Manual Trigger  For testing in n8n editor

  Check Telegram   Code Node       Single code block: calls Telegram
  Updates1                         getUpdates API, extracts callback_query +
                                   message actions, routes by type. Key
                                   pattern: all logic in ONE node.

  Route by Type    Switch Node     Routes to: Approval Branch
                   (Rules)         (approve/reject/publish/kill) OR ORBIT
                                   Branch (platform selection)

  --- APPROVAL                     
  BRANCH ---                       

  Process Approval Code Node       Determines action type (approve / reject /
                                   publish / kill). Extracts brief_id,
                                   content_log_id.

  Update Brief     PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- UPDATE content_briefs SET
  Status                           status = \[action\] WHERE id =
                                   \[brief_id\]

  Telegram Confirm Code Node       Sends confirmation message to Telegram
                                   (\'Brief approved!\' / \'Brief rejected!\'
                                   etc.)

  Check If         Code Node       IF action == \'approve\' → continue to E2.
  Approved                         IF action == \'publish\' → skip to E3. IF
                                   action == reject/kill → stop.

  Call E2 Webhook  Code Node       POSTs to E2 webhook with brief_id +
                   (httpRequest)   brief_data to trigger content generation

  Link Content to  PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- UPDATE content_briefs SET
  Brief                            content_log_id = \[id\] WHERE id =
                                   \[brief_id\]

  Send Content     Code Node       Pulls content from \'Call E2 Webhook\'
  Preview          (httpRequest)   node result. Sends full 10-field content
                                   preview to Telegram with \[Publish\]
                                   \[Kill\] buttons.

  Call E3 Webhook  Code Node       POSTs to E3 webhook when operator taps
                   (httpRequest)   Publish, triggering video production

  --- ORBIT BRANCH                 
  ---                              

  ORBIT Process    Code Node       Handles platform selection callbacks
                                   (tiktok/instagram/linkedin/all/hold).
                                   Builds schedule_logs payload.

  ORBIT Execute    PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- INSERT rows into
  Update                           schedule_logs (status: queued) for each
                                   selected platform

  ORBIT Telegram   Code Node       Sends Telegram confirmation of scheduling
  Confirm                          (e.g. \'Queued for TikTok + Instagram
                                   ✅\')
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Key Pattern:** Check Telegram Updates1 uses single Code node --- all
Telegram polling and routing in one JavaScript block. Avoids n8n
multi-node data passthrough issues.

**6.4 ELECTRON-2 Content Generator (v1)**

The AI content engine. 15 nodes in a linear chain. Generates full
content package through Qdrant knowledge retrieval → Claude Sonnet 4 → 3
QA Gates → PostgreSQL storage.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**        **Detail**
  (exact)**                        
  ---------------- --------------- ------------------------------------------
  Webhook          Webhook         POST --- triggered by Brief Approval
                                   Handler \'Call E2 Webhook\' node

  Webhook Parse    Code Node       Extracts brief data from webhook body:
  Brief                            topic, module, platform, funnel, duration,
                                   brief_id

  When clicking    Manual Trigger  For testing
  \'Execute                        
  workflow\'                       

  Parse Brief      Set Node        Manually set brief fields for testing:
  (manual)                         module, platform, funnel, topic, duration

  CorpFit Qdrant   Qdrant Vector   Semantic search on funfit_brand_rules
                   Store           collection. Returns 15 most relevant brand
                                   rules. Uses Embeddings Ollama sub-node
                                   (nomic-embed-text).

  Embeddings       Ollama          nomic-embed-text model at ollama:11434 ---
  Ollama           Embeddings      for brand rules semantic search

  Get Banned       Qdrant Vector   Loads all 71 entries from
  Phrases          Store           funfit_banned_phrases collection. Uses
                                   Embeddings Ollama1 sub-node.

  Embeddings       Ollama          nomic-embed-text model at ollama:11434 ---
  Ollama1          Embeddings      for banned phrases load

  Assemble Prompt  Code Node       Merges: static core (\~1,200 words) +
                                   dynamic CTA rules (B2C/B2B) + platform
                                   tone block + 15 brand rules + 71 banned
                                   phrases + brief. Output: systemPrompt +
                                   userMessage.

  Call Claude API  Code Node       Calls Anthropic API. Model:
                   (httpRequest)   claude-sonnet-4-20250514. max_tokens:
                                   4096. temp: 0.7. Captures actual
                                   input_tokens + output_tokens from
                                   response.usage.

  Parse Output     Code Node       Extracts 10 structured fields from Claude
                                   raw text: hooks(3), script, onscreen_text,
                                   storyboard, caption_short, caption_long,
                                   cta, disclaimer

  Banned Phrase    Code Node       Scans ALL 10 content fields against all 71
  Check                            banned phrases. Output: qa_passed (bool) +
                                   violations list.

  QA Gate 1 Health Code Node       Haiku 4.5 --- health claims check: medical
                   (httpRequest)   advice, cure language, guaranteed
                                   outcomes. CRITICAL severity.

  QA Gate 2 Brand  Code Node       Haiku 4.5 --- brand tone check:
                   (httpRequest)   platform-aware Fun Test, DO NOT FAIL safe
                                   list, lenient template. HIGH severity.

  QA Gate 3        Code Node       Haiku 4.5 + 6 hard-coded checks: CorpFit
  Audience         (httpRequest)   in CTA, CorpFit in captions, no \'free\',
                                   B2C/B2B CTA match, no FunFit. HIGH
                                   severity.

  Format for       Code Node       Structures all 28 columns for PostgreSQL
  Storage                          INSERT. Calculates e2_cost, qa_cost,
                                   total_cost from actual token counts.

  Store to         PostgreSQL Node insert --- writes full content record to
  content_logs                     content_logs (28 columns)

  Webhook Response Respond to      Returns content JSON to calling workflow
                   Webhook Node    (Brief Approval Handler). MUST use this
                                   node --- webhook trigger set to \'Using
                                   Respond to Webhook Node\'.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.5 ELECTRON-3 Video Producer (v1)**

Pure linear 8-node chain. Receives content_log_id, fetches data, routes
to correct video tool, generates video, stores result, notifies
Telegram.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**        **Detail**
  (exact)**                        
  ---------------- --------------- ------------------------------------------
  E3 Webhook       Webhook         POST --- triggered by Brief Approval
  Trigger                          Handler \'Call E3 Webhook\' node when
                                   operator taps Publish

  Load Content     Code Node       Extracts content_log_id + brief_id from
                                   webhook payload

  Fetch Content    PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- SELECT content_logs JOIN
  from DB                          content_briefs WHERE content_logs.id =
                                   \[content_log_id\]

  Select Video     Code Node       Routing logic: module + funnel + platform
  Tool                             → video tool. Returns: tool name + API
                                   params + prompt.

  Generate Video   Code Node       Calls selected tool\'s API: Kling via
                   (httpRequest)   fal.ai (909a576d\...) / HeyGen / Synthesia
                                   / Veo / Pika. Polls until complete.

  Store to         PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- INSERT into publish_logs
  publish_logs                     (video_tool, video_url, resolution,
                                   duration, status=ready_to_post)

  Telegram Preview Code Node       Sends video URL + content summary to
                   (httpRequest)   Telegram. Video URL + brief details
                                   formatted for operator review.

  Webhook Response Respond to      Returns result to calling workflow
                   Webhook Node    
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.6 ELECTRON-4 Scheduler (v1)**

Runs on schedule, detects ready videos, performs quality check, reads
ORBIT mode, sends platform selection to Telegram, creates schedule_logs
entries.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**        **Detail**
  (exact)**                        
  ---------------- --------------- ------------------------------------------
  Schedule Trigger Schedule        Runs every 5 minutes (or configured
                   Trigger         interval)

  When clicking    Manual Trigger  For testing
  \'Execute                        
  workflow\'                       

  Fetch Ready      PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- SELECT from publish_logs
  Videos                           WHERE status = \'ready_to_post\'

  If               If Node         Checks if Fetch Ready Videos returned any
                                   rows. true → proceed. false → stop
                                   (nothing to schedule).

  Video Quality    Code Node       Verifies: resolution ≥ 1080p, format =
  Check                            MP4, duration within platform limits. 3
                                   retries with exponential backoff (2s, 4s,
                                   6s).

  Get ORBIT Mode   PostgreSQL Node executeQuery --- SELECT value FROM
                                   system_config WHERE key = \'orbit_mode\'.
                                   Returns: manual / semi / auto.

  Send ORBIT       Code Node       Sends Telegram message with platform
  Telegram         (httpRequest)   selection buttons: \[TikTok\]
                                   \[Instagram\] \[LinkedIn\] \[All\]
                                   \[Hold\]. 3 retries with backoff.

  Insert Schedule  Code Node       POSTs to Dashboard Actions webhook.
  Logs             (httpRequest)   Creates schedule_logs row(s) for selected
                                   platforms (status: queued). Error-logger
                                   on failure.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.7 ORBIT Publisher (v1 --- Workflow ID: bzC27k33)**

Minimal 4-node design. All publishing intelligence is consolidated in
the single ORBIT Processor Code node --- same single-node pattern as
Check Telegram Updates1.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**    **Detail**
  (exact)**                    
  ---------------- ----------- ------------------------------------------
  Schedule Trigger Schedule    Runs every 5 minutes
                   Trigger     

  When clicking    Manual      For testing + manual /orbit Telegram
  \'Execute        Trigger     command
  workflow\'                   

  Webhook Trigger  Webhook     POST --- allows external trigger via
                               /webhook/orbit-publish URL

  ORBIT Processor  Code Node   All logic in one block: (1) Fetch queued
                   (single)    items from dashboard-api (2) Mark
                               status=\'publishing\' (3) Call platform
                               API \[TikTok/IG/LinkedIn\] (4) Update to
                               \'published\' + store post_id/url OR
                               increment retry_count (5) Send per-item +
                               summary Telegram notifications
