developer accounts are registered.

**6.8 Dashboard API (v1)**

Simple 4-node read-only API. Powers all data display in the Cloudflare
Worker dashboard.

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**     **Detail**
  (exact)**                     
  ---------------- ------------ ------------------------------------------
  Webhook          Webhook      GET --- receives requests from Cloudflare
                                Worker dashboard frontend

  Query All Data   PostgreSQL   executeQuery --- runs comprehensive SQL
                   Node         across all tables: counts, recent briefs,
                                content_logs, publish_logs, schedule_logs
                                (with JOIN), error_logs

  Format Response  Code Node    Structures query results into
                                dashboard-friendly JSON object

  Respond to       Respond to   Returns formatted JSON to Cloudflare
  Webhook          Webhook Node Worker
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.9 Dashboard Actions (v1)**

5-node POST handler. Executes all write operations triggered from
dashboard buttons or other workflows.

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Node Name      **Type**     **Detail**
  (exact)**                     
  ---------------- ------------ ------------------------------------------
  Webhook          Webhook      POST --- receives action requests from
                                dashboard UI or internal workflows

  Process Action   Code Node    Parses action type from body: approve /
                                reject / publish / kill /
                                create_schedule_log / update_schedule_log
                                / etc. Builds appropriate SQL.

  Execute Action   PostgreSQL   executeQuery --- runs the mutation SQL
                   Node         generated by Process Action

  Format Response  Code Node    Structures result into JSON response
                                (success: true, affected rows, etc.)

  Respond to       Respond to   Returns result to caller
  Webhook          Webhook Node 
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------

