**13. n8n TECHNICAL PATTERNS**

**13.1 Critical Rules**

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Pattern**      **✅ Correct Way**                        **❌ Wrong Way**
  ---------------- ----------------------------------------- -------------------------------
  HTTP requests in this.helpers.httpRequest()                fetch() or axios --- not
  Code nodes                                                 available in n8n sandbox

  Cross-node data  \$(\'NodeName\').first().json.fieldName   Direct variable access or
  references                                                 \$json after RETURNING \*

  Webhook +        Set trigger to \'Using Respond to Webhook Default setting (causes timeout
  Response nodes   Node\'                                    on webhook calls)

  Workflow         Linear chain (A→B→C→D)                    Split connections from single
  sequences                                                  node (causes data passthrough
                                                             issues)

  SQL string       Separate raw\_ fields (display) + sql\_   Same escaped value for both
  escaping         fields (INSERT)                           display and INSERT

  Action string    Accept BOTH \'publish\' AND \'published\' Exact match only --- misses
  matching                                                   some callback variations

  QA gates         Inline Code nodes inside E2 workflow      Sub-workflows --- data
                                                             passthrough bugs caused
                                                             failures

  Telegram polling getUpdates with offset tracking           Webhook (requires public URL,
                                                             breaks in dev)
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**13.2 Common Gotchas**

-   Webhook POST data: always wrapped in body object --- check
    items\[0\].json.body

-   PostgreSQL RETURNING \*: replaces \$json in downstream nodes ---
    must use \$(\'NodeName\').first().json

-   Telegram callback vs command: need allowed_updates:
    \[\'callback_query\', \'message\'\] for both

-   Field name mismatches: always verify names between connected nodes
    (e.g., primary_tool vs video_tool)

-   Content deduplication: inject existing topics into LLM prompt, NOT
    database matching

-   n8n credentials: \'Postgres account\' credential ID =
    q7zxG97pdUIHmNnO (separate from \'Read Top Trends\' credential)

**13.3 Error Handling Pattern**

Try-catch around all API calls

→ On error: POST to Error Logger webhook (/webhook/error-logger)

→ Error Logger: INSERT to error_logs table

→ Telegram notification with error type + message

→ Retry with exponential backoff (2s, 4s, 6s for critical nodes)

**13.4 Workflow Update Process (via API)**

-   1\. GET workflow: POST to n8n.corpfit.cloud/rest/workflows/{id} ---
    capture versionId

-   2\. Deactivate: POST /rest/workflows/{id}/deactivate with current
    versionId

-   3\. Update: PATCH /rest/workflows/{id} with new definition

-   4\. Reactivate: POST /rest/workflows/{id}/activate with updated
    versionId

**Login payload:** Uses \'emailOrLdapLoginId\' field (not \'email\') for
authentication.

