**15. ANTI-PATTERNS & NON-NEGOTIABLES**

**15.1 Technical Anti-Patterns**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **❌ Never**                   **✅ Instead**
  ------------------------------ ----------------------------------------
  fetch() in n8n Code nodes      this.helpers.httpRequest()

  Direct variable refs across    \$(\'NodeName\').first().json.field
  nodes                          

  Same escaped string for SQL +  Separate raw\_ (display) and sql\_
  display                        (INSERT) fields

  Exact action string match only Accept both tenses (publish / published)

  Complex DB matching for dedup  Inject existing topics into LLM prompt

  Sub-workflows for QA gates     Inline QA gates in E2 workflow

  Default webhook trigger        \'Using Respond to Webhook Node\' when
  setting                        Response node exists

  Split connections from one     Linear sequential chains
  node                           

  Local AI models for complex    Claude API --- llama3.2/3.1 failed on
  prompts                        3,300-word prompts
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**15.2 Content Non-Negotiables**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Rule**              **Detail**
  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  NO medical advice     No diagnose, prescribe, treat, cure, or
                        guaranteed health outcomes

  NO \'free\' in CTAs   Hard-coded Gate 3 check --- will always FAIL

  NO \'FunFit\'         Old brand name --- must be CorpFit in all content
  anywhere              and UI

  NO B2B CTAs on B2C    \'Book a demo\' must never appear in B2C
  content               (TikTok/Instagram) content

  NO publishing without All 3 gates must pass or content is blocked
  QA pass               

  NO engagement-only    \'Save this\' alone is not enough --- must pair
  CTA for B2C           with \'Download CorpFit\'

  \'CorpFit\' MUST      Gate 3 hard-coded check for each location
  appear in CTA, short  
  caption, and long     
  caption               
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**15.3 Dashboard / Code Rules**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Rule**              **Detail**
  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  Never say \'free\' in B2C: \'Download CorpFit\' \| B2B: \'Book a demo\'
  CTAs                  

  Always use DXA for    WidthType.PERCENTAGE breaks in Google Docs
  table widths          

  Use ShadingType.CLEAR ShadingType.SOLID causes black backgrounds
  for table cells       

  Cloudflare Worker     wrangler deploy --- never edit production JS
  deploy                directly

  n8n workflow backup   Export JSON before any modification --- QUANTUM
                        Backup Manager runs daily
